                  </persName>
            . I am a tailor, and work for Mr. Gordon in the Strand. On Saturday the 22 d of June the prisoner offered me a coat for sale, for 2 l. 2 s. - I bought it, and wore it - I gave it to Clements.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220911-221-person2091">
                  THOMAS 
                  CLEMENTS
               <interp inst="t18220911-221-person2091" type="surname" value="CLEMENTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-221-person2091" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-221-person2091" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. Bennet gave me the coat. I apprehended the prisoner, and told him the charge; he said he would tell the truth; that it was stolen from the shop; he did not say by whom. I afterwards took him to Bennett's; the prosecutor went into the house; he then said,</p>
               <p>"The truth is, I did sell it to the young man where that gentleman is gone."</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
